node.text: ⚠️AMAZING KITTEN RESCUE!⚠️ During our recent trip to Greece, my friends @everchanginghorizon and @jess.wandering rescued the cutest little kitten that was abandoned on a cliffside and I was honored to be able to help too after getting introduced to @zawf.zante.gr an incredible animal rescue charity that desperately needed more funding to help save more animals! I donated 1,000 euros to them on the spot, but we have also created a @karmagawa fundraiser with the goal of raising $25,000 to get them a full on shelter and veterinarian on their staff because there are SO many more animals in Zakynthos that need URGENT help so please donate what you can, share this video with your followers and tag people, celebrities and influencers who need to see and share this too and let’s all work together to raise the $25k ZAWF needs to help more animals in need! Sadly, this little kitten didn’t make it and that’s why we MUST get these poor animals more help faster in the future…see my stories for the link to the @karmagawa Facebook fundraiser and ALL donations great and small are most appreciated! #helpanimals #savethekitties #zakynthos #animalrescue

node.text: ⚠️SHARE TO HELP SAVE OUR PLANET BEFORE IT’S TOO LATE⚠️Repost from @karmagawa We humans are destroying our environment and wildlife in so many different ways as this sad but accurate cartoon replaces the roles of humans and animals in today’s society to show us all a different perspective and if there’s any hope of saving our planet and too many endangered species before it’s too late, then we MUST confront these issues RIGHT NOW and that starts with education and spreading awareness to everyone! So, watch this video a few times as it covers many of the methods in which we’re destroying the only planet we all have and really think about its message because it’s 100% true and sadly it’s future generations of humans and animals that will suffer the greatest consequences of our irresponsible behavior, especially if we do nothing and allow all of this destruction to continue. We MUST work together and fight for our planet and our wildlife so please share this video with your followers and tag people, celebrities and influencers in the comments who need to see it and share it with their followers too — it’s not too late for us to change our ways, all our wildlife and our planet deserves it! Great video by Steve Cutts and music by Kina #saveourplanet #climatechange #globalwarming #endanimalcruelty #karmagawa

node.text: Repost from @karmagawa We love this video that’s all about the power of people helping each other, coming together and the beauty of the human spirit even during this difficult time! Thank you to our frontline healthcare workers, nurses, doctors, pharmacy staff, grocery store clerks, farmers, delivery drivers, military service members, restaurant workers, police and firefighters, truck drivers, teachers, factory and warehouse workers, bank tellers, mail carriers, transportation workers, generous neighbors, living-room-concert performers and budding sidewalk-chalk artists delivering messages of joy — we are SO grateful for you all! Thank you for your love, dedication, kindness and for giving yourself and your time to serve those of us in need and all those we love. Thank you for all that you do that we know, and all that you do that we will never know. Thank you for the long hours and sleepless nights. Thank you for coming to work every day to make a difference in the lives of those around you. We are eternally grateful for you ALL. WE LOVE YOU and HONOR YOU. “Nothing can dim the light that shines from within.” — Maya Angelou. Please share this video with your followers and tag people who need to see it, let’s all cheer each other up during this crisis! Video Credit: @todayshow Music Credit: @andradaymusic #coronavirus #socialdistancing #quarantine #karmagawa

node.text: I’ve lived a crazy life and been fortunate enough to be able to fulfill all my childhood dreams and more. My mission these days is all about helping others live their dream lives too, teaching them to become millionaires through stock trading along with my @karmagawa charity’s mission to build schools all over the world and also helping the environment through my @savethereef project...and I’m only able to do all this while traveling nonstop because I’ve focused on what I love and put my entire being into every project I take on. Too many depressed people message me every day because they’re busy building other people’s dreams...please stop doing that! Maximize this extraordinary time in history and utilize all the new tools and technology that is revolutionizing education like never before! Thank you @iamjoelbrown for this great video, sorry for making so many jokes throughout the interview :) #throwbackthursday #buildyourowndreams #jewsinthejungle

node.title: My Best Piece Of Advice For People Everywhere

node.text: Repost from @karmagawa Here’s why we are SO proud for Karmagawa to support animal rescue centers like @animalaid_india all over the world as they help so many animals in need! Please share this video with your followers and tag people, influencers and celebrities who need to see it as four small puppies came close to losing their lives in a horrendous accident when they stumbled into spilled tar in a garbage pile, but thanks to the hard work of some kind-hearted individuals these puppies were saved! When the first one wandered in and got stuck in the tar, she must have cried so much that the others came to see what was the matter, and they too got glued down by the awful tar. We knew they had a mother, but we couldn't find her until the day after their rescue and the hours-long process of removing the tar with oil and dish soap. These poor puppies were dazed with confusion, pain, fear and frustration, and two were so completely covered that all they could move was their eyes. But by the time Mommy arrived, they were freed from the poisonous grip of the tar and ready for the comfort of her love! We ALL must do what we can to help animals whenever possible…share this story with your followers and let’s inspire everyone to make this a better planet for humans and animals alike! #helpanimals #kindnessmatters #karmagawa

node.title: Saving Puppies From A Tragic Accident

node.text: This is why I LOVE animals so much!!! Repost from @karmagawa  A baby elephant was stuck upside down in a gutter, while a pride of lions were closing in…but elephants are truly amazing creatures so watch what happens and please share this video with your followers and tag someone who needs to see it as videos like this help show how incredible animals are so WE MUST DO A BETTER JOB PROTECTING THEM! Roughly 100 elephants die every day and at the current rate they will be extinct in the next decade or so…we need to get the word out before it’s too late as the empathy of elephants never ceases to amaze us! Great video @newsnercom #savetheelephants #animalsrock #karmagawa

node.title: Baby Elephant Is Stuck Upside Down

node.text: Happy birthday to my mom today as she is literally the best mom I, or anyone else, could ever ask for! Everything I am and everything I achieve in life is due to her incredible love, dedication, sacrifice and her heartfelt guidance over the years, not to mention the self-confidence she’s helped instill in me. Because she taught me to always believe in myself and that I could achieve anything I wanted in life (as long as I dreamt big and worked my butt off every day) and her nonstop caring for me is something I’m truly grateful for. To those who say I just got lucky in the stock market, I say the harder I’ve worked the luckier I’ve gotten over the years, just like my now 20+ millionaire students too! But I definitely owe my crazy work ethic to my mom, so I guess they’re not wrong that I am very lucky in life — they just don’t realize my luck all comes down to having such an incredible mom and dad behind me all these years…and in the future as we’re a family business too! And I love how many of my students and friends know my mom too so I’d appreciate everyone wishing her a happy birthday in the comments here so she can see just how many people we’re able to reach through my stock market lessons and now with the amazing @karmagawa and @savethereef communities too! #happybirthday #bestmomever #ilovemymom #mommasboy

node.text: It’s been an interesting challenge lately trying to keep up with the red hot stock market while also getting back to traveling so I’ve had to get creative…whatcha think of my mobile office here in this brand new van designed by the one and only @everchanginghorizon that allows me to truly work and trade with some incredible views? While I truly am grateful for all the opportunity, but it’s been a grind day and night to work from different timezones around the world as I split my time on @karmagawa @savethereef along with creating new watchlists, video lessons, trade alerts, commentary, blog posts, tweets and webinars for my students…you name it I do it because I remember how confusing the stock market was for me in the beginning of my career as I never had any mentor or guide so I’m here to be the teacher to my students that I never had! My only question is how dedicated will you be in your studies?! I don’t teach lazy students…SO HOW BAD DO YOU WANT SUCCESS?! #ilovemyjob #workfromanywhere #laptoplifestyle #mobileoffice

node.text: ⚠️URGENT ISSUE RIGHT NOW⚠️ Repost from @savethereef This man was caught littering a river with thousands of plastic water bottles and while he’s been arrested and faces up to a year in jail for his water pollution, his crime will impact wildlife and the environment for centuries since plastic does not decompose quickly. Police are also still searching for his accomplices so let’s all share this video to help the police find the other polluters in this video! And what’s worse is that this same kind of irresponsible polluting is carried by countless individuals and companies worldwide so much so that by 2050 it’s estimated there will be 900+ million tons of plastic in the ocean which is more than the weight of all the fish in the sea! It’s just absolutely heartbreaking to see and our beaches, oceans, rivers and birds, animals and marine life deserve better SO WE MUST STOP THIS RIGHT NOW! Please use your social media platform for good and share this important post with your followers and tag people, celebrities, influencers and news media who need to see it so they can share too & let’s all spread awareness about this URGENT issue and condemn disgusting polluting like this before it’s too late! Video by @get.waste.ed #plasticpollution #stoplittering #karmagawa #savethereef

⚠️SCARY BREAKING NEWS, PLEASE SHARE AS WE MUST TREAT OUR PLANET BETTER!⚠️ Repost from @karmagawa A fire just broke out in the Gulf of Mexico after an underwater pipeline leaked. Multi-billion dollar petroleum company Pemex, recently ranked the 7th most polluting company in the world, said a gas leak was discovered in the 12-inch submarine pipeline near a platform in the Ku-Maloob-Zaap oil field. Pemex, which has a long record of major industrial accidents at its facilities, said it would investigate the cause of the fire, but refused to comment any further. And while Pemex would love to sweep their latest environmental disaster under the rug and go on with their booming business as usual, WE MUST ALL SPEAK UP AND STATE THAT WE WILL NOT TOLERATE THIS ANY MORE! Our oceans and marine life deserve FAR better so please use your social media platform to spread awareness about this, share this post with your followers and tag people, celebrities, influencers and new media who need to see this and share it too, dangerous companies like Pemex MUST be held responsible for incidents like this or else they’ll just keep happening, killing more and more of our precious wildlife and environment every time…ENOUGH IS ENOUGH! #pemex #oilfield #fire #saveouroceans #saveourplanet #karmagawa

node.text: Today is the 3 year anniversary of @karmagawa and we want to thank EVERYONE in the community for your support! My co-founder @badboi and I are so grateful for everyone joining us in our mission to make this a better planet for humans and animals alike and now in just 3 years now we have built 86 schools/libraries, produced 3 documentaries and donated over $6 million to over 65 charities that build medical centers, rescue injured animals, save endangered species and protect the environment (oil spills, climate change, plastic pollution and coral reefs) and feed children/families in need. Our goal is to support 1,000+ charities and build 1,000+ schools/libraries so we’re only just getting started, but well on our way to achieving our big goals in time! And more than just the donations, the @karmagawa community has become one of the largest charities on all of social media as we raised over $1 million in online fundraisers last year, our charity merch regularly selling out and our social posts, along with our @savethereef project, now getting upwards of 50,000, 100,000 and sometimes even 500,000 or 1+ million shares as spreading awareness about these URGENT issues is the first step in finding potential solutions! So, thank you again for your support, we’re SO EXCITED to see what more we can accomplish when we all work TOGETHER! #happyanniversary #teamwork #givingback #charity #karmagawa

node.text: ⚠️PLEASE SHARE WITH YOUR FOLLOWERS TO HELP END ANIMAL CRUELTY!⚠️ Repost from @karmagawa This video of a large elephant pulling a tree that has been cut down is going viral on social media because it exemplifies two urgent issues we MUST confront right now: ending both animal cruelty and deforestation! While the location of this video has not been revealed, this sad scene plays out every hour of every day as animals all over the world are treated terribly with very little food or water and forced to do extreme manual labor in harsh conditions. WE MUST WORK TOGETHER TO STOP THIS CRUELTY RIGHT NOW! Please use your social media platform for good and share this video with your followers and tag people, celebrities, influencers and news media who need to see it and share it too as we MUST all remind EVERYONE that we MUST stop animal cruelty like this…animals, especially endangered animals deserve SO MUCH BETTER! Thanks for sharing lambe_turah #endanimalcruelty #animalsdeservebetter #savetheelephants #karmagawa

node.text: ⚠️AMAZING KITTEN RESCUE!⚠️ During our recent trip to Greece, my friends @everchanginghorizon and @jess.wandering rescued the cutest little kitten that was abandoned on a cliffside and I was honored to be able to help too after getting introduced to @zawf.zante.gr an incredible animal rescue charity that desperately needed more funding to help save more animals! I donated 1,000 euros to them on the spot, but we have also created a @karmagawa fundraiser with the goal of raising $25,000 to get them a full on shelter and veterinarian on their staff because there are SO many more animals in Zakynthos that need URGENT help so please donate what you can, share this video with your followers and tag people, celebrities and influencers who need to see and share this too and let’s all work together to raise the $25k ZAWF needs to help more animals in need! Sadly, this little kitten didn’t make it and that’s why we MUST get these poor animals more help faster in the future…see my stories for the link to the @karmagawa Facebook fundraiser and ALL donations great and small are most appreciated! #helpanimals #savethekitties #zakynthos #animalrescue

node.text: ⚠️WARNING: DO NOT TRY DOING THIS YOURSELF!⚠️Swipe over to see more shots of this INSANE view here in Greece, who did it better — me or @jess.wandering?? Also understand that while she loves crazy cliffs like this, I’m still just trying to overcome my childhood fear of heights so while I’ll admit she crushed me in terms of style, I’ll happily take a moral victory here that I even got out there in the first place considering how windy this spot and the 1,000+ foot drop below! Even @everchanginghorizon was surprised I was dangling my laptop over the edge like that, but screw it, you only live once so sometimes you have to push yourself and I really will do ANYTHING to show off the #laptoplifestyle to help more people realize you do NOT have to work in an office/cubicly these days, get out and explore more as the world is a truly fascinating place! I REALLY do not encourage others to try this as it’s dangerous, but at the same I filmed a badass video lesson here and my job as a teacher means that I have to do WHATEVER I can to show my students new perspectives/life-changing lessons so tell me whatcha think of this #officewithaview and if you will watch the truly crazy video lesson I filmed here! #mobileoffice #workfromanywhere #laptops
